Confluence appears to be forcing minimum column width, as of the latest OD version.

h5.Steps to reproduce
# create a Page;
# in a Section, add two columns, with width set to 1200 px and 400px;
# save the Page and view it.

*Result in Confluence 5.3-OD-11:* page is displayed correctly;
*Result in Confluence 5.3-OD-12:* a horizontal scroll bar is added to the Section.

(see screenshots)

This behaviour does not change in different browsers or display sizes.

This was raised in the linked support ticket.

{quote}
Heading 1 and Heading 2 no longer display a horizontal line
All headings in general appear to be smaller than before
Whitespace margins are missing above headings placed on the first line of Section macros
{quote}

When using Confluence Image search you can restrict the search within a single Space or you can search the entirety of Confluence Spaces if you want.

However, the search does not work as expected for some image names.

Here's some examples:
Key-word: {{Wnter}}
!Wnter.png|thumbnail!
Returns 3 related images. {color:green}(correct){color}

As the images have also the word {{Wild}}:
!Wild.png|thumbnail!
Returns 0 related images.

Key-word: {{Mgic}}
!Mgic.png|thumbnail!
Returns 2 related images. {color:green}(correct){color}

The images also contains {{Universe}}
!Universe.png|thumbnail!
Returns 0 related images.

Key-word: {{1391}}
!1391.png|thumbnail!
Returns 3 related images. {color:green}(correct){color}

The images also contains {{0992}}
!0992.png|thumbnail!
Returns 0 related images.

It seems like the search always find the related images if the queried word is at the beginning of the image name, something that does not happened when searching for words within its middle or tail.
Sometimes it does not work even if the queried string is the same as the image name.

h3. Problem

When the administrator change the character encoding from UTF-8 to UTF-16 at the general configuration page. The confluence page will then render in chinese character.

In confluence log you will only see :
{code}
2014-10-15 05:26:03.000265500 2014-10-15 05:26:02,998 WARN [TP-Processor32] [atlassian.confluence.themes.DefaultThemeManager] extractTheme Unable to find configured theme module: com.atlassian.studio.confluence:studio
2014-10-15 05:26:03.000267500  -- url: /wiki/admin/flyingpdf/configurepdflanguagesupport.action | userName: sysadmin
{code}

To verify this is the problem run in the database:
{noformat}
SELECT BANDANAVALUE FROM BANDANA where BANDANAKEY = 'atlassian.confluence.settings';
{noformat}
if it returns a different value of UTF-8 in the result, then it is affected.


h3.Steps to reproduce:
# Set up a new Confluence
# Go under the _Administrator Panel > General Configuration > Formatting and International Settings_﻿ and change _Encoding_ field from UTF-8 to UTF-16.

*Expected Result:*
Confluence doesn't allow the change
*Actual Result:*
Confluence becomes unusable, styles are broken and administration sections are locked.
Can't be reverted back unless a DB change is done.


h3. Workaround 
# Check on database to confirm whether it is in UTF-16
{code}
select * from bandana where bandanakey = 'atlassian.confluence.settings';
{code}
# Update the database to UTF-8
{code}
update bandana set bandanavalue = replace(bandanavalue, '<defaultEncoding>UTF-16</defaultEncoding>', '<defaultEncoding>UTF-8</defaultEncoding>') where bandanakey = 'atlassian.confluence.settings';
{code}

